# WaveLinux — Session Init Summary

A barebones priming doc for any future session. Loaded first; everything
else (README, ROADMAP, code) builds on this.

## What it is

A PyQt6 desktop mixer for PipeWire on Linux. It mimics Elgato Wave Link:
two master buses (Monitor + Stream), per-channel dual faders (one for
what you hear, one for what gets streamed), per-channel effects, per-app
output routing, and a dedicated virtual recording device for OBS.

Single user-process app. No daemon, no system service, no root, no
direct libpipewire binding — talks to PipeWire over `pactl`, `pw-dump`,
`wpctl`, and `parec` subprocesses.

## Source layout (repo root: WaveLinux/)

- `main.py` (~3140 lines) — Qt UI, dialogs, channel strips, app-routing
  tab, tray, settings, update checker, scene wiring. Owns the
  PipeWireEngine instance.
- `pipewire_engine.py` (~3300 lines) — virtual sink/source creation,
  loopback routing, FX chain spawning, snapshot caching, event
  subscriber, LADSPA probe, app-name resolution (10-step identity
  chain), system-sound bucketing, hostname filtering.
- `wavelinux_theme.py` — Qt stylesheet (dark, cyan/violet accents).
- `install.sh`, `uninstall.sh`, `start.sh`, `PKGBUILD` — packaging.
- `README.md`, `ROADMAP.md` — user docs / status.
- `icon.png` — 512x512 app icon.

## Architecture facts that matter

- **Two master buses**: 🎧 Monitor (routable to any non-WaveLinux sink)
  and 📡 Stream (locked to virtual sink `wavelinux_mix_stream`, exposed
  to OBS as `WaveLinux-Stream`). Each is null-sink + virtual-source on
  the monitor.
- **Channels**: user virtual sinks (`wavelinux_<name>`) + every real mic
  / hardware source surfaced. Each has a MON fader and a STR fader,
  optional Link to move them together.
- **Per-app routing**: `app_routing[<app_name>] = sink_name`. Persisted
  in config. Stale entries pruned after `app_prune_days` (default 14).
  Auto-routing on first sight via `_auto_routed_indices` — moves a
  stream once when it appears on the wrong sink, then leaves it alone
  so manual pavucontrol moves stick.
- **System Sounds bucket**: streams with `media.role = event`,
  notification apps (canberra, paplay, kdialog, etc.) are all grouped
  under a single permanent "System Sounds" row in app routing, like
  Wave Link's System entry. Always visible even when idle.
- **Effects per channel**: RNNoise, HighPass, EQ (3-band), Compressor,
  Gate, Limiter. Built-ins use PipeWire's `bq_*` filters; the others
  are LADSPA (`swh-plugins`, `noise-suppression-for-voice`).
- **FX implementation**: `set_channel_fx` builds ONE unified config
  per channel via `_build_unified_chain_config` and spawns ONE
  `pipewire -c <conf>` client. The config's `filter.graph` lists every
  enabled effect as a node (namespaced `s<idx>_<id>`) with explicit
  `links` chaining them together. Result: one virtual sink (`*.input`)
  + one virtual source (`*.source`) per channel regardless of effect
  count. Uses `_effect_stage_blocks` for per-effect config generation.
- **Clipguard** is no longer a master-bus button — it's the per-mic
  `Limiter` effect inside the unified chain. Old `clipguard: true`
  configs are migrated to per-mic `limiter` on first load if a
  `selected_mic` is present.
- **Branding rule**: every value WaveLinux writes into
  `device.description` / `node.description` / `node.nick` /
  `media.name` / `application.name` is whitespace-free
  (`WaveLinux-Voice-Chat`, not `WaveLinux Voice Chat`). Internal sink
  names (`sink_name=`) stay underscore-style (`wavelinux_voice_chat`).
- **State key**: per-channel saved state is keyed by PipeWire
  `node.name` so it survives a PipeWire restart.
- **Volume ceiling**: 100% everywhere (`PipeWireEngine.MAX_VOLUME`),
  even though PipeWire allows 150%.
- **Refresh model**: 2 s poll backstop + `pactl subscribe` event stream
  with 150 ms debounce + per-tick snapshot cache (`EngineSnapshot`)
  that runs each heavy command exactly once.
- **Peak meters**: one `parec --raw --format=s16le --channels=1` per
  visible strip, parsed on the Qt event loop (~40 Hz).
- **In-app update checker**: `UpdateChecker` class polls GitHub releases
  API on startup (background, non-blocking via queue + QTimer polling).
  Handles 404 (no releases yet) gracefully.

## App name resolution (10-step identity chain)

The `_process_sink_input` method resolves a human-readable name for each
audio stream. Steps are tried in order, first match wins:

1. **GIO_LAUNCHED_DESKTOP_FILE** — walks PID parent chain for this env
   var, set by KDE/GNOME on every .desktop-launched process. Survives
   Electron/Chromium renderer subprocesses.
2. **Sandbox detection** — Flatpak ID, Snap name, cgroup scopes,
   AppImage mount paths.
3. **Reverse-DNS app IDs / icon names** — checked against both
   `_BINARY_DISPLAY_NAMES` table and `_KNOWN_APP_IDS` canonicaliser.
   `application.process.host` is deliberately NOT checked here (that's
   the hostname, not an app).
4. **.desktop index** — looks up PID's binary basename in a cached
   index of all installed `.desktop` files.
5. **application.name** — from PulseAudio properties, skipped if generic.
6. **application.process.binary** — checked against
   `_BINARY_DISPLAY_NAMES` (e.g. `spotify` → `Spotify`).
7. **PID walk** — `/proc/<pid>/exe` basename + comm + ppid chain,
   with `_infer_name_from_exe` for install-path inference.
8. **Direct property fallbacks** — snap.name, node.description,
   node.nick, node.name, media.name.
9. **Last resort generic** — accepts even generic-named properties to
   ensure every stream gets a row.
10. **Absolute fallback** — `Audio Stream #<id>` so nothing is silently
    dropped.

Hostname filtering: streams whose final resolved name matches the
machine hostname (via `_host_aliases`) are filtered out to prevent
"DuskyPC" appearing in app routing.

`_BINARY_DISPLAY_NAMES` maps ~40 common binary names to friendly
display names (brave-browser → Brave, spotify → Spotify, etc.).

## File system locations

- Settings: `~/.config/wavelinux/config.json` (atomic writes via temp +
  `os.replace`).
- App log: `~/.config/wavelinux/wavelinux.log`.
- Per-effect logs: `~/.config/wavelinux/fx-logs/`.
- PipeWire client confs we generate:
  `~/.config/pipewire/wavelinux-fx-*.conf`,
  `~/.config/pipewire/wavelinux-rnnoise-*.conf`,
  `~/.config/pipewire/wavelinux-chain-*.conf`.
- Single-instance lock: `~/.wavelinux.lock`.
- Autostart: `~/.config/autostart/wavelinux.desktop`.

## Target distro / runtime

Tested on CachyOS / Arch with KDE. Requires PipeWire ≥ 0.3 with
WirePlumber, `pipewire-pulse`, `libpulse` (for pactl/parec),
`swh-plugins`, and the AUR `noise-suppression-for-voice` plugin for
RNNoise. Optional: `carla` for VST/LV2 hosting via right-click menu.

## CachyOS audio stack (relevant defaults)

- **PipeWire + WirePlumber** is the stock audio stack.
- Stock WirePlumber configs live in `/usr/share/wireplumber`. User
  overrides go in `/etc/wireplumber/` or `~/.config/wireplumber/` as
  `.conf` snippets.
- **Bluetooth profile auto-switching is ON by default**:
  `bluetooth.autoswitch-to-headset-profile = true`. The moment any
  client opens an input stream on a Bluetooth device, WirePlumber
  flips it from A2DP → HSP/HFP. The high-fidelity A2DP **sink
  disappears** while the headset profile is active. Disable per-user
  with `wpctl settings --save bluetooth.autoswitch-to-headset-profile
  false`.
- Initial profile after pairing: `a2dp-sink` by default.
- Diagnostic command (CachyOS FAQ):
  `journalctl --user -u pipewire -u pipewire-pulse -u wireplumber -b 0`.

## Git conventions

- Default branch: `master`.
- All work goes directly on `master` or is merged via PR into `master`.

## What has been done (PR history, most recent first)

### PR #25 — App routing rework + update checker fixes
- Reworked app identity chain to 10-step priority system (GIO desktop
  file → sandbox → reverse-DNS → .desktop index → binary table → PID
  walk → fallbacks). First match wins, no more multi-pass.
- Added `_resolve_via_gio_env` — reads GIO_LAUNCHED_DESKTOP_FILE from
  process tree, survives Electron/Chromium renderer subprocesses.
- Added `_identify_via_desktop` — cached .desktop file index lookup.
- Added `_BINARY_DISPLAY_NAMES` table for native app resolution
  (spotify → Spotify, brave-browser → Brave, etc.).
- Grouped system/notification sounds under permanent "System Sounds"
  bucket (canberra, paplay, kdialog, plasma-pa, etc.).
- Every sink-input now guaranteed visible — "Audio Stream #N" fallback
  prevents silent drops.
- Hostname filtering — streams resolving to machine hostname are hidden.
- Fixed update checker: replaced QTimer.singleShot-from-thread with
  queue.SimpleQueue + QTimer polling (fixes "stuck on checking").
- Fixed AppRoutingRow X button: self.window() inside QDialog returned
  the dialog, not WaveLinuxWindow — now passes explicit main_win ref.
- Fixed live app detection: refresh runs when settings dialog is open
  even if main window is hidden to tray.
- Filtered "Media Stream #N" phantom entries from app_routing on save
  and load.

### PR #24 — In-app update checker + native stream fixes
- Added in-app update checker polling GitHub releases API.
- Fixed `/proc/<pid>/exe` (not comm) for long binary names.
- Seeded node.id from pw-dump pw_id so native PipeWire streams aren't
  dropped from app routing.

### PR #23 — App routing phantom entries + Spotify + Brave
- Fixed phantom `#None` entries in app routing.
- Fixed Spotify misidentification (native/AUR package).
- Fixed Brave and Ferdium not appearing in app routing.

### PR #22 — Mic input filter + internal FX node hiding
- Actually filter mic input from app routing list.
- Hide internal WaveLinux FX nodes from user-facing lists.

### PRs #19–21 — App routing detection rewrite
- Rewrote app routing detection to use pw-dump as primary source.
- Resolved app streams to real names instead of collapsing to "Audio
  Src" / "Audio Source".
- Normalized generic-name comparisons (case-insensitive, whitespace/
  hyphen-insensitive) so all variations of "audio src" are filtered.

### PRs #15–18 — Widget scaling
- Channel strips scale with window height (not just width).
- Reduced wasted padding in header, audio sources, and master panel.
- Strips shrink proportionally before horizontal scroll activates.

### PR #14 — Comment cleanup
- Trimmed narrative/journal-style comments, tightened docstrings.

### PR #13 — FX chain fixes
- Fixed limiter self-monitor routing bug.
- Fixed LADSPA port-name mismatches.
- Fixed SC4 compressor stereo channel handling.

### PRs #10–12 — Unified FX chain + audit pass
- Unified per-channel filter-chain: one `pipewire -c` process per
  channel regardless of how many effects are enabled.
- Moved Clipguard from master-bus to per-mic limiter effect.
- BT locked to A2DP for session duration.
- Hostname normalizer + persistent forget-blocklist.
- Full 4-tier audit pass (critical → low fixes).

## What is explicitly NOT planned

Stream Deck integration, drag-and-drop reorder, true Wayland global
hotkeys, ducking (no usable PipeWire sidechain primitive), Flatpak
manifest. See ROADMAP.md "Explicitly not planned".
